{"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.NormCast.Ext","instances":[{"typeNames":["Eq","Tactic.NormCast.Label"],"name":"Tactic.NormCast.instDecidableEqLabel","className":"Decidable"},{"typeNames":["Tactic.NormCast.Label"],"name":"Tactic.NormCast.instReprLabel","className":"Repr"},{"typeNames":["Tactic.NormCast.Label"],"name":"Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedLabel","className":"Inhabited"},{"typeNames":["Tactic.NormCast.NormCastExtension"],"name":"Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedNormCastExtension","className":"Inhabited"}],"imports":["Init","Lean","Mathlib.Tactic.NormCast.CoeExt","Mathlib.Tactic.RunCmd"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L142-L190","name":"Tactic.NormCast.Attr.normCast","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.Attr.normCast","doc":"The `norm_cast` attribute should be given to lemmas that describe the\nbehaviour of a coercion in regard to an operator, a relation, or a particular\nfunction.\n\nIt only concerns equality or iff lemmas involving `↑`, `⇑` and `↥`, describing the behavior of\nthe coercion functions.\nIt does not apply to the explicit functions that define the coercions.\n\nExamples:\n```lean\n@[norm_cast] theorem coe_nat_inj' {m n : ℕ} : (↑m : ℤ) = ↑n ↔ m = n\n\n@[norm_cast] theorem coe_int_denom (n : ℤ) : (n : ℚ).denom = 1\n\n@[norm_cast] theorem cast_id : ∀ n : ℚ, ↑n = n\n\n@[norm_cast] theorem coe_nat_add (m n : ℕ) : (↑(m + n) : ℤ) = ↑m + ↑n\n\n@[norm_cast] theorem cast_coe_nat (n : ℕ) : ((n : ℤ) : α) = n\n\n@[norm_cast] theorem cast_one : ((1 : ℚ) : α) = 1\n```\n\nLemmas tagged with `@[norm_cast]` are classified into three categories: `move`, `elim`, and\n`squash`. They are classified roughly as follows:\n\n* elim lemma:   LHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coe\n* move lemma:   LHS has 1 head coe and 0 internal coes,    RHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coes\n* squash lemma: LHS has ≥ 1 head coes and 0 internal coes, RHS has fewer head coes\n\n`norm_cast` uses `move` and `elim` lemmas to factor coercions toward the root of an expression\nand to cancel them from both sides of an equation or relation. It uses `squash` lemmas to clean\nup the result.\n\nOccasionally you may want to override the automatic classification.\nYou can do this by giving an optional `elim`, `move`, or `squash` parameter to the attribute.\n\n```lean\n@[simp, norm_cast elim] lemma nat_cast_re (n : ℕ) : (n : ℂ).re = n := by\n  rw [← of_real_nat_cast, of_real_re]\n```\n\nDon't do this unless you understand what you are doing.\n\nA full description of the tactic, and the use of each lemma category, can be found at\n<https://lean-forward.github.io/norm_cast/norm_cast.pdf>.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L139-L139","name":"Tactic.NormCast.Attr.normCastLabel","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.Attr.normCastLabel","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L130-L136","name":"Tactic.NormCast.addInfer","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.addInfer","doc":"`addInfer decl` infers the label of `decl` and adds it to the cache.\n\n* elim lemma:   LHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coe\n* move lemma:   LHS has 1 head coe and 0 internal coes,    RHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coes\n* squash lemma: LHS has ≥ 1 head coes and 0 internal coes, RHS has fewer head coes\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L118-L122","name":"Tactic.NormCast.addSquash","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.addSquash","doc":"`addSquash decl` adds `decl` as a `squash` lemma to the cache. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L111-L115","name":"Tactic.NormCast.addMove","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.addMove","doc":"`addMove decl` adds `decl` as a `move` lemma to the cache. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L106-L108","name":"Tactic.NormCast.addElim","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.addElim","doc":"`addElim decl` adds `decl` as an `elim` lemma to the cache. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L99-L99","name":"Tactic.NormCast.normCastExt","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.normCastExt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L97-L97","name":"Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedNormCastExtension","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedNormCastExtension","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L93-L97","name":"Tactic.NormCast.NormCastExtension","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.NormCastExtension","doc":"The `norm_cast` attribute stores three simp sets. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L87-L87","name":"Tactic.NormCast.pushCastExt","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.pushCastExt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L62-L85","name":"Tactic.NormCast.classifyType","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.classifyType","doc":"Classifies a declaration of type `ty` as a `norm_cast` rule. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L58-L59","name":"Tactic.NormCast.countInternalCoes","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.countInternalCoes","doc":"Count how many coercions are inside the expression, excluding the top ones. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L46-L55","name":"Tactic.NormCast.countCoes","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.countCoes","doc":"Count how many coercions are inside the expression, including the top ones. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L38-L43","name":"Tactic.NormCast.countHeadCoes","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.countHeadCoes","doc":"Count how many coercions are at the top of the expression. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L27-L35","name":"Tactic.NormCast.getSimpArgs","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.getSimpArgs","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L25-L25","name":"Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedLabel","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.instInhabitedLabel","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L25-L25","name":"Tactic.NormCast.instReprLabel","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.instReprLabel","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L25-L25","name":"Tactic.NormCast.instDecidableEqLabel","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.instDecidableEqLabel","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.lean#L21-L25","name":"Tactic.NormCast.Label","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/NormCast/Ext.html#Tactic.NormCast.Label","doc":"`label` is a type used to classify `norm_cast` lemmas.\n* elim lemma:   LHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coe\n* move lemma:   LHS has 1 head coe and 0 internal coes,    RHS has 0 head coes and ≥ 1 internal coes\n* squash lemma: LHS has ≥ 1 head coes and 0 internal coes, RHS has fewer head coes\n"}]}